OL,3,C'How hard is it to bake a potato?' -
OL,4,CHeadteacher criticises food at his
OL,5,Cschool
OL,7,FMr Ashley said he had no control over
OL,8,Fthe food on offer to pupils and said
OL,9,Fthere had been a lack of progress made
OL,10,Fafter talks with the company.
OL,12,F"Frankly, the food that is served in
OL,13,Fthe canteen is completely
OL,14,Funacceptable, so much so, that if my
OL,15,Fown children's school served this I
OL,16,Fwould be exceptionally unhappy," Mr
OL,17,FAshley wrote."
